<NEW>

There was no interruption, WHEELIE was allowed to go perch himself on
top of the structure they had been inside of. It was relatively flat
at the top, with stairs leading up to it. Had this been a truely
religious place, this might have been the area were sacrifices were
made to angry god's and were mortals feared to tread except at the
behest of the priests. However there was none of that, there was only
stone and metal and the debris that had landed on it like leaves and
such. It made for a nice place for WHEELIE to sit.

Time passes . . .

Eventually the shape of ASTRA could be seen climbing up the stair, her
optics glowing slightly as the sun above was begining to set. She
stopped as she saw WHEELIE, "Oh, you're up here. I would not want to
intrude."

She turned as if to leave.

(TAG)

Preston
